PEOPLE ex rel. SMITH v. WEEKES, Town Clerk. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. September 28, 1903.) Proceéding by the people of the state of New York, on the relation of Charles Smith, against H. Luther Weekes, town clerk of the town of Hempstead.

Argued before GOODRICH, P. J„ and BARTLETT, JENKS, WOODWARD, HIRSCHBERG, and HOOKER, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed,.on authority of In re Seaman, 175 N. Y. 506, 67 N. E. 1090, without costs.
